### Tested versions

v4.5.dev.custom_build [9e636ba4a] based on my PR https://github.com/godotengine/godot/pull/107529

but it is also reproducible in the normal 4.5 version (and it's worse because the lists of comment and text delimiters get mixed up and change order with each change)

### System information

Windows 11

### Issue description

When using the `is_in_comment` and `is_in_string` functions of the `CodeEdit` node, the values ​​returned are not always correct.

In the original version, the returned value is almost random because the index of the items in each list is changed with each addition (or attempt to add with the bug that prevents adding items to the Array) or with each modification, moreover the two lists are stored in a single large delimiter list, and in the original version the two lists also change place in this large list.

In my PR version, items no longer change index, just like lists in the big list, which makes the bug easier to fix, because the last thing that makes this bug exist is the way `_is_in_delimiter` checks and returns its values. With the indexes no longer changing, the only problem now is for `delimiter_comments` which sees its indexes added to the number of items in `delimiter_strings`.

In the example screenshot, the values ​​returned by `is_in_string` are correct, but not the one from `is_in_comments`.

![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/fa148024-d8fe-4e65-8510-8cb5483e3790)


Here is the script used in the control node:

```gdscript

extends Control

@onready var code_edit: CodeEdit = %CodeEdit


func _on_code_edit_caret_changed() -> void:
	print("-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------")
	print("Is in string (column provided): ", code_edit.is_in_string(code_edit.get_caret_line(), code_edit.get_caret_column(0)), " | Tested on line: ", code_edit.get_line(code_edit.get_caret_line(0)), " and with result intended: ", custom_is_in_string(code_edit.get_caret_line(), code_edit.get_caret_column(0)))
	print("Is in comment(column provided): ", code_edit.is_in_comment(code_edit.get_caret_line(), code_edit.get_caret_column(0)), " | Tested on line: ", code_edit.get_line(code_edit.get_caret_line(0)), " and with result intended: ", custom_is_in_comment(code_edit.get_caret_line(), code_edit.get_caret_column(0)))
	print("Is in string (no column provided): ", code_edit.is_in_string(code_edit.get_caret_line()), " | Tested on line: ", code_edit.get_line(code_edit.get_caret_line(0)), " and with result intended: ", custom_is_in_string(code_edit.get_caret_line()))
	print("Is in comment(no column provided): ", code_edit.is_in_comment(code_edit.get_caret_line()), " | Tested on line: ", code_edit.get_line(code_edit.get_caret_line(0)), " and with result intended: ", custom_is_in_comment(code_edit.get_caret_line()))



func custom_is_in_string(line: int, column := -1) -> int:
	return custom_is_in_delimiter(line, column, "String")

func custom_is_in_comment(line: int, column := -1) -> int:
	return custom_is_in_delimiter(line, column, "Comments")

func custom_is_in_delimiter(line: int, column: int, delimiter_type: String) -> int:
	if delimiter_type == "String":
		return code_edit.is_in_string(line, column)
	else:
		if code_edit.is_in_comment(line, column) == -1 :
			return -1
		else:
			return code_edit.is_in_comment(line, column) - len(code_edit.delimiter_strings)
```

### Steps to reproduce

Use the project in the ZIP.

### Minimal reproduction project (MRP)

[debug_project_2025-06-17_21-00-34.zip](https://github.com/user-attachments/files/20782190/debug_project_2025-06-17_21-00-34.zip)

### Tested versions

- Reproducible in 4.5 dev 5
- Reproducible in 4.4.1 stable

### System information

Void #1 SMP PREEMPT_DYNAMIC Sun May 11 04:22:51 UTC 2025 on X11 - X11 display driver, Multi-window, 1 monitor - OpenGL 3 (Compatibility) - NVIDIA GeForce GTX 970 (nvidia; 570.144) - Intel(R) Core(TM) i5-7600K CPU @ 3.80GHz (4 threads)

### Issue description

Using the depth texture as the albedo on an unshaded object in Forward+ or Compatibility results in the object essentially being invisible:

![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/f639810e-36ad-4e96-bafd-4c28be59c7df)

Only in Compatibility if you enable glow in the environment, the applied texture becomes very dark:

![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/79a5c376-0446-4319-ae39-46ca27da6bf3)

From testing it seems like the texture is almost exactly 4x darker after enabling glow.

### Steps to reproduce

- Make project using Compatibility
- Apply the following shader to an object:
```glsl
shader_type spatial;
render_mode unshaded;

uniform sampler2D screen_texture : hint_screen_texture;

void fragment() {
	ALBEDO = (texture(screen_texture, SCREEN_UV).rgb);
	//ALBEDO *= 4.0;
}
```
- Enable glow

### Minimal reproduction project (MRP)

N/A

Fixes https://github.com/godotengine/godot/issues/83896 
Fixes https://github.com/godotengine/godot/issues/95872


- Change the display of `Line Lenght Guidlines`, `Delimiter Strings`, `Delimiter Comments`, `Code Completion Prefixes` and `Indent Automatic Prefixes` so we cant change their types (which would not have worked in all cases and would display an error message) and make easier to delete a value.
- Fix the bug that prevents adding values ​​to `Code Completion Prefixes`,  `Delimiter Strings`, `Delimiter Comments` and `Indent Automatic Prefixes`.
- Make the  `Delimiter Strings` and `Delimiter Comments` list dont change order when you do a litlle changement.
- Make `Line Length Guidlines`value unable to be less to 0.
- Update documentation to help on unclear stuff about Array manipulation.

